An Act relative to the determination of need of new technology.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 25B of chapter 111 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
2 Edition, is hereby amended by striking out the definition of “New technology”, and inserting in
3 place thereof the following definition:-
4 ''New technology'', equipment such as magnetic resonance imagers and linear
5 accelerators, as may be defined by the department, or a service, as may be defined by the
6 department, which for reasons of quality, access or cost is determined to be new technology by
7 the department; provided, however, that computerized tomography and any equipment that is
8 widely utilized as standard diagnostic, treatment or therapeutic technology shall not be
9 considered new technology.
